commentBody:
@Vaer

Good point, so I take back that there’s no revealer. The problem with a short revealer like that is that if you get the four crosses first, you never even see it. 

And that’s what happened in my case.

@Steve L

Regarding "pronouncing" the revealer:
The clue said "parsed differently", so I think it's meant to be read as "I'M D.B."

@Steve L
DAVID BOWIE was an actor as well as a singer. He was in plenty of movies, including The Hunger and The Prestige. My favorite is Labyrinth.

I should go on an 80's puppety fantasy movie binge...

@Steve L

I don't know what "never even see it" means in this context.  The clue was there, regardless of the order of solving.  (I got it last, after everything was filled in, and found the denouement perfect.)

I'm on board with the "bad day" theory. ;)

@B

It means all four crosses were gimmes and so I never looked at the clue or the anser for 73A.

I'm not sure why this is unclear.

@Steve L

So is it the puzzle's fault you didn't read the revealer clue or its answer?

It's not.  Weird to be in opposite sides for a change, on a Tuesday no less.  On to tomorrow...

@live your life
Those were the only 2 I'd heard of also, but the other 2 filled in easily enough from the  crosses. So no look- ups needed.
Took me longer than my Tuesday average by a fair bit, but I enjoyed it. Did I mention the no look- ups aspect?

@Nate
I have one of those, too.  Somehow I got a 5:21 PB for a Saturday!!  That's about the same as my PB for Monday!  My Saturday average is closer to 39 minutes.

